What's unique about the personal repository online is that it's completely up to the user who should have access to that type of information.
The company calls it ‘personal data authorisation’.
The idea behind Inrupt is according to the company's CEO, John Bruce, that the company should provide resources, process and relevant competence to make Solid available to all.
The company consists in the moment of Berners-Lee, Bruce, a security platform purchased by IBM, some hired developers on contract to work with the project and a team of volunteer programmers.
